what it is to forget.

108
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:25,053
No, you don't know
what it is to forget.

109
00:11:25,891 --> 00:11:29,918
Like you, I am endowed with memory.
I know what it is to forget.

110
00:11:30,028 --> 00:11:34,089
No, you are not endowed with memory.

111
00:11:34,232 --> 00:11:38,293
Like you, I too have struggled
with all my might

112
00:11:39,037 --> 00:11:40,800
not to forget.

113
00:11:41,540 --> 00:11:44,202
Like you, I forgot.

114
00:11:47,913 --> 00:11:52,043
Like you, I longed
for a memory beyond consolation,

115
00:11:53,084 --> 00:11:55,848
a memory of shadows and stone.

116
00:11:56,021 --> 00:11:59,684
For my part I struggled
every day with all my might

117
00:12:00,025 --> 00:12:02,687
against the horror
of no longer understanding

118
00:12:02,861 --> 00:12:05,386
the reason to remember.

119
00:12:05,530 --> 00:12:08,966
Like you, I forgot.

120
00:12:15,774 --> 00:12:20,143
Why deny the obvious necessity
of remembering?

121
00:12:25,383 --> 00:12:28,147
Listen to me.
I know something else.

122
00:12:28,253 --> 00:12:29,880
It will begin again.

123
00:12:29,955 --> 00:12:34,483
200,000 dead and 80,000 wounded
in nine seconds.

124
00:12:34,593 --> 00:12:38,393
Those are the official figures.
It will begin again.

125
00:12:38,630 --> 00:12:43,533
It will be 10,000 degrees on the earth.
Ten thousand suns, people will say.

126
00:12:43,602 --> 00:12:46,036
The asphalt will burn.

127
00:12:46,137 --> 00:12:49,038
Chaos will prevail.

128
00:12:49,140 --> 00:12:51,938
An entire city will be lifted
off the ground,

129
00:12:52,043 --> 00:12:54,204
then fall back to earth in ashes.

130
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:02,345
New vegetation rises
from the sands.

131
00:13:03,555 --> 00:13:06,718
Four students await together,
like brothers,

132
00:13:06,791 --> 00:13:09,658
a legendary death.

133
